API stands for Application Programming Interface
it allows one piece of software to talk to another

REST stands for Representaional State Transfer

Usually a Rest API works the same way a website does. You make a call of a client to a server
and get data from a http request.

www.facebook.com/youtube

made an api requequest to facebooks graph api
www.graph.facebok.com/youtube   

filter the data using parameters
www.graph.facebok.com/youtube?fields=id,name,likes   

maps.gooogleapis/maps/api/json
server is maps.google.apis.com
resource is /maps, /api, /json

instagram.com/developer
click api console

GET request is used to consume data
POST request  accepts the data enclosed in the body of the request message

Intal postman rest client

